{"type":"message","id":"01cef4d9","parentId":"1a197cbb","timestamp":"2026-04-07T11:05:00.161Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Grasping the Basics**\n\nI've got the initial instructions down pat! It seems the core approach to Feishu plugin issues is running `/feishu doctor` within the Feishu chat. Alternatively, I can execute a shell command, provided the troubleshooting process offers one. Simple enough, but the real challenge is figuring out what to do *if* the troubleshooting path is unavailable.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a4226ade8f428f2c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node /Users/hh/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/dist/doctor.js 2>/dev/null || echo \"not found\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":3922,"output":47,"cacheRead":113900,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117869,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775559892795,"responseId":"chatcmpl-e5b754cd-caf9-40a9-8d89-728e71f1f8b1"}}
