{"type":"message","id":"7683ffff","parentId":"cfb2652d","timestamp":"2026-04-07T11:09:53.919Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Analyzing 400 Errors**\n\nI'm getting 400 errors when pinging `open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping`, which indicates that my `appId` or `appSecret` might be incorrect. It's also possible that the bot is either unreleased or its permissions are improperly configured. I need to investigate the authentication credentials and the bot's status to resolve this.\n\n\n**Authenticating the Credentials**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the authentication credentials. My investigation into the `appId` and `appSecret` is a top priority, as any error there would lead directly to the 400 error I'm seeing. I'll be checking these values against the known correct configurations to eliminate them as the potential cause.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_623227c36ec93a16","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/credentials/lark.secrets.json"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":28258,"output":195,"cacheRead":32553,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61006,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775560190116,"responseId":"chatcmpl-4810929d-9949-4c8d-8f7a-c8409f6b4500"}}
