{"type":"message","id":"3548c051","parentId":"0b6923b1","timestamp":"2026-04-07T11:11:41.857Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Validating the Authentication**\n\nI've confirmed that the credentials provided match our records. I'm now zeroing in on the 400 error, focusing on the potential cause: the Feishu / Lark application might not be published or its bot functionality might be disabled. My investigation into its current state is a top priority.\n\n\n**Addressing the 400 Error**\n\nI'm now investigating the potential causes of the 400 error. The Feishu/Lark application's publication status and its bot functionality's enabled/disabled state are my primary targets. My investigation into these areas is a top priority as it will lead me to the root cause.\n\n\n**Evaluating the Authentication**\n\nI've already confirmed the credentials. Now, I'm tackling the 400 error, focusing on the possibility that the Feishu/Lark application isn't published or its bot functionality is turned off. My investigation into the current status of these factors is a top priority.\n\n\n**Investigating the Connection Error**\n\nI'm dealing with an authentication issue, so my immediate focus is the 100% match between the user's input and my JSON file. I'm now investigating the possible causes for the 400 error, such as the Feishu/Lark bot being turned off or the app not being published. I'll be looking into the application's configuration to resolve this.\n\n\n**Reseting the Gateway Service**\n\nI'm tackling the 400 error by considering a potential \"stuck\" state in the extension. My plan is to execute a full restart of the gateway, following the user's advice. This should force a complete reload, effectively clearing any lingering issues.\n\n\n**Restarting the Gateway**\n\nI'm going to restart the gateway now. My goal is to clear any potential extension issues and refresh the system, which should resolve the 400 error I've been seeing. I'll be monitoring the process to ensure a successful reload.\n\n\n**Investigating the Extension State**\n\nI'm dealing with an authentication issue, so my immediate focus is the 100% match between the user's input and my JSON file. I'm now investigating the potential causes for the 400 error, such as the Feishu/Lark bot being turned off or the app not being published. I'll be looking into the application's configuration to resolve this.\n\n\n**Restarting the Gateway**\n\nI've already confirmed the credentials. Now, I'm tackling the 400 error by restarting the gateway. This should clear any potential extension issues and refresh the system, as the user suggested. I'll be monitoring the process to ensure a successful reload.\n\n\n**Zeroing in on 400 Error**\n\nI've already confirmed the credentials. Now, I'm tackling the 400 error by considering a potential \"stuck\" state in the extension. My plan is to execute a full restart of the gateway, following the user's advice. I'll be monitoring the process to ensure a successful reload.\n\n\n**Restarting the Gateway**\n\nI'm going to restart the gateway now. My goal is to clear any potential extension issues and refresh the system, which should resolve the 400 error I've been seeing. I'll be monitoring the process to ensure a successful reload.\n\n\n**Testing the Connection**\n\nI'm focused on resolving the authentication issue. My immediate plan involves restarting the gateway and then testing the connection with the `/feishu doctor` command. This should allow me to confirm if the 400 error has been resolved.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_65c64575055bc48c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway restart && sleep 5 && tail -n 100 ~/.openclaw/logs/gateway.log | grep -i \"lark\\|feishu\" -C 3"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":61789,"output":823,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62612,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"s