{"type":"message","id":"38ad3340","parentId":"15eba340","timestamp":"2026-04-07T11:27:40.860Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8f9b77ab41d1669d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"'Host: open.feishu.cn\\r\\n' +\n      host: 'open.feishu.cn',\n  'receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in:\\n' +\n2026-04-07T19:17:30.427+08:00 [feishu] stopping feishu[default]\n2026-04-07T19:17:30.428+08:00 [feishu] stopped feishu[default]\n2026-04-07T19:17:30.429+08:00 [feishu] feishu[default]: bot open_id resolved: unknown\n2026-04-07T19:17:30.430+08:00 [feishu] feishu[default]: WebSocket client started\n2026-04-07T19:18:03.146+08:00 [feishu] starting feishu[default] (mode: websocket)\n2026-04-07T19:18:03.148+08:00 [feishu] feishu[default]: message dedup enabled (ttl=43200000ms, max=5000)\n2026-04-07T19:18:03.149+08:00 [feishu] feishu[default]: starting WebSocket connection...\n      url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n        'Host: open.feishu.cn\\r\\n' +\n      host: 'open.feishu.cn',\n      url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n        'Host: open.feishu.cn\\r\\n' +\n      host: 'open.feishu.cn',\n  'receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in:\\n' +\n      url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n        'Host: open.feishu.cn\\r\\n' +\n      host: 'open.feishu.cn',"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":25,"aggregated":"'Host: open.feishu.cn\\r\\n' +\n      host: 'open.feishu.cn',\n  'receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in:\\n' +\n2026-04-07T19:17:30.427+08:00 [feishu] stopping feishu[default]\n2026-04-07T19:17:30.428+08:00 [feishu] stopped feishu[default]\n2026-04-07T19:17:30.429+08:00 [feishu] feishu[default]: bot open_id resolved: unknown\n2026-04-07T19:17:30.430+08:00 [feishu] feishu[default]: WebSocket client started\n2026-04-07T19:18:03.146+08:00 [feishu] starting feishu[default] (mode: websocket)\n2026-04-07T19:18:03.148+08:00 [feishu] feishu[default]: message dedup enabled (ttl=43200000ms, max=5000)\n2026-04-07T19:18:03.149+08:00 [feishu] feishu[default]: starting WebSocket connection...\n      url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n        'Host: open.feishu.cn\\r\\n' +\n      host: 'open.feishu.cn',\n      url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n        'Host: open.feishu.cn\\r\\n' +\n      host: 'open.feishu.cn',\n  'receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in:\\n' +\n      url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n        'Host: open.feishu.cn\\r\\n' +\n      host: 'open.feishu.cn',","cwd":"/Users/hh/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775561260854}}
{"type":"message","id":"98eec2da","parentId":"38ad3340","timestamp":"2026-04-07T11:28:11.436Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Analyzing the User's Image and the Error**\n\nThe user has provided an image showing their Feishu Developer Console. The configuration is indeed set to \"长连接\" (Long connection), just as we told them to. So why is the connection still failing with the error message: `receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in...`?\n\nLet's carefully read the error message again: \"receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in...\". This implies that the app itself needs to be a \"Self-build\" app to use this feature.\n\nIs it possible that the AppID provided by the user is actually for a \"Store APP\" (商店应用) or something else?\n\nWait. The user showed the \"事件与回调\" page. It literally says \"使用长连接接收事件 推荐\" and has a \"已添加事件\" section which lists \"机器人进群\". So the console lets them turn it on... but the *ping* to the websocket fails complaining it's only supported for self-build apps?\n\nLet's double check how feishu distinguishes apps. There's \"Custom App\" (企业自建应用) and \"Store App\" (商店应用). If it was a Store App, would that option even be available?\n\nAnother possibility is that the plugin `openclaw-lark` is hitting the *wrong endpoint* or is constructing the request wrong for this specific type of app. Let's look at the request in the log.\n`POST /open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` -> Wait, what is `openclaw_bot/ping`? No, wait... That URL doesn't look like an official Feishu endpoint. No, wait. Is there a Feishu endpoint `https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping`? Or wait, maybe this is not the WebSocket connection logic but rather some specific ping logic inside the SDK or OpenClaw? No, OpenClaw SDK probably uses the standard endpoints. Wait... `POST /open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` doesn't sound right if we are talking about WebSockets. Wait! The Feishu WS endpoint is usually negotiated via `POST /open-apis/corehr/v1/leave_types` or something? No, it's `POST /open-apis/ws/v2/endpoints`.\n\nWait, the error from Feishu is explicitly: `receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app`.\n\nLet's look at the Feishu documentation or think about the App configuration.\n\nLook closely at the image the user uploaded.\n\n\"事件配置\"\n\n\"订阅方式\" - \"使用 长连接 接收事件 推荐\"\n\n\"已添加事件\" -> only ONE event is added: `im.chat.member.bot.added_v1` (机器人进群).\n\nWait! The OpenClaw plugin also requires `im.message.receive_v1` (接收消息) in order to actually receive messages. The user *has not* added `im.message.receive_v1` (接收消息) to the events list! That's why I can't receive messages!\n\nBut wait, why the `400` error and the message `receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app. Configured in: ...`?\n\nLet's read the full error message in the logs. Actually, it says `Configured in:\\n` but we didn't see what's after `Configured in:`...\n\nLet me look at the API call: `POST /open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` ... no no, the first log line says `url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping'`. What is `openclaw_bot/ping`? It seems like some endpoint that the plugin is calling? No... maybe it's hitting a strange URL?\nActually... there is no standard Feishu endpoint like `/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping`. Let me check the openclaw-lark source code if possible, or just ignore that specific URL path (could be a custom API mock or an internal SDK ping thing? Wait... Feishu's long connection SDK might use `POST /open-apis/ws/v2/endpoints`).\nWait, looking closer at the logs:\n```\n      url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n```\nActually, is this what OpenClaw-lark uses? Wait, that URL strongly implies something is hardcoded wrong, OR it's from a completely different error block and it is just printing. Wait! I don't see `/ws/v2` anywhere. But the log string explicitly says `'receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in:\\n' + ...`.\n\nWait, if you create an app in Feishu, there is a difference between \"Custom Apps\" (企业自建应用) and \"Store Apps\" (网页应用/小程序 etc.? No). \"Store Apps\" are 商店应用.\nDid they create an \"企业自建应用\"? If they did, then why does Feishu return that error?\nMaybe they didn't \"publish\" the app? The console has a \"版本管理与发布\" tab. If they changed settings there but didn't publish, the token will be bound to the *published* version which might have different settings (or the backend thinks it's a different type)?\nActually, wait. If they *didn't* publish, the long-connection setting isn't live. They must create a version and publish it. The UI says \"已添加事件\" -> `机器人进群`... but they *must* add `接收消息` too. And they must PUBLISH.\n\nLet's review the image.\nThe side bar on the left:\n- 权限管理\n- 事件与回调\n- 安全设置\n- 测试企业和人员\n- 版本管理与发布\n\nIf this was a *Self-built App* (企业自建应用), the menu structure is exactly as shown. But why is Feishu returning \"only available in self-build & Feishu app\"? Is this because it needs to be enabled in \"测试企业和人员\" or it needs to be published (App version)?\nActually, there's another subtle point. Is the App disabled? No. Is it possible the OpenClaw-Lark plugin has a bug where it misidentifies the domain or the tenant?\n\nWait, why did I ask them to check if it's a self-built app? I said \"只有自建应用（且只对你们自己企业/租户内部使用）才被允许\". They might have created a \"商店应用\" (Store App) by mistake. Let's look at the screenshot. A self-built app normally has `cli_XXX`. Wait, Store Apps also have `cli_XXX`!\nBut wait, if you are a Store App, you have to configure \"Subscription\", \"Gadget\", etc. The sidebar for Store Apps looks slightly different, having \"应用上架\" (App Release) maybe? The sidebar says \"应用发布 -> 版本管理与发布\" which is typical for Self-built Apps.\n\nOkay, let's revisit the events.\nIn the screenshot, under `已添加事件` (Added Events), the ONLY event listed is `机器人进群` (`im.chat.member.bot.added_v1`).\nI specifically instructed:\n`- ⚠️ 核心检查：添加事件：必须确保包含（订阅）了：\n- 接收消息 (im.message.receive_v1)`\n\nThey *missed* this step. They have NOT added `接收消息`. That's why I can't receive messages!\n\nBut wait, would missing `接收消息` cause the 400 error and the \"only available in self-build...\" error?\nActually, what if the error message is a known Feishu limitation? \"receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app\" -> This happens if the app's `appId` does not match the token's expected app type?\nAnother case: The user provided `cli_a95e7a8914ba5cc2`. This is their app ID.\nIs it possible that long connections are only available for apps that are fully published, or where the \"测试企业和人员\" is not set to use test credentials while the main credentials are used? Oh! Feishu has \"Test Version\" and \"Production Version\". If they are using the App ID / App Secret of the production version, but the app isn't published yet, the API might reject the request because the production version doesn't exist or is empty!\nActually, Feishu provides a pair of \"Test App ID/Secret\" and \"Prod App ID/Secret\"? No, App ID is the same, but the App Secret is different? No, App Secret is the same. What differs is whether you use the test tenant.\n\nLet's verify the exact error message from Feishu SDK/API docs.\n\"receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app\" -> This means \"长连接只能用于企业自建应用或飞书官方应用\".\nIf the user's app IS a self-built app (which the UI suggests), why does Feishu say otherwise?\nAh... \"Configured in:\"\nWait. Could the `appId` in the config be WRONG? The user said:\n`cli_a95e7a8914ba5cc2`\n`FnzZDL7YmMnFB2Pr1rXovcitjz6Cv13V`\nAnd the `lark.secrets.json` has `FnzZDL7YmMnFB2Pr1rXovcitjz6Cv13V`.\nWait, what about the `appId` in `openclaw.json`?\nLet's check what `openclaw.json` has for `appId`!\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_86d293de2294abf6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | grep -i \"appId\\|cli_\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":691,"output":2280,"cacheRead":64980,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67951,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775561260861,"responseId":"chatcmpl-854847cf-5d48-4add-a26a-ed195768153f"}}
