{"type":"message","id":"e01ec21e","parentId":"f66ffe0d","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:32:45.381Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. The user asks to remember to reply in Chinese (\"全部使用中文\"). I already have a USER.md setting this up, but I should explicitly confirm and add it to `SOUL.md` or `MEMORY.md` if not already prominent.\n2. The user also mentions they didn't receive my message on Feishu and asks if I can see theirs.\n3. The logs confirm precisely that **Feishu is STILL forcefully rejecting the WebSocket connection** because of the exact same error:\n`'receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in:\\n... Developer Console ... Events and Callbacks'`\n\nIf the openclaw gateway hasn't picked up the change, maybe it's because Feishu itself hasn't applied the published version to the App ID yet?\nWait, if the user \"Published\" the app right now, does the new token / app configuration take time to propagate on Feishu's end? Usually it's immediate.\nDid the user click **\"发布\" (Publish)**? They said \"都加上了\" (Added them all). But did they actually go to the \"版本管理与发布\" page, create a version and hit publish? Often people just hit save on the \"事件与回调\" page and assume it's done.\nI must state emphatically again that neither am I receiving their messages, nor can they receive mine, because the OpenClaw plugin cannot establish the websocket connection. The connection throws 400 with the \"only available in self-build...\" error.\nI will write to USER.md updating the language constraint, and explain the physical reality of the Feishu connection block.\n\nLet me first update their USER profile or SOUL profile.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1578a98149f87aff","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"- **语言限制**: 无论任何情况，全部使用中文（Simplified Chinese）回答。\" >> ~/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usa