{"type":"message","id":"813a7203","parentId":"474f508f","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:33:50.179Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Still receiving exactly `receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app`.\n\nWhy on earth would Feishu return this error for a published, self-built app using its AppID and AppSecret?\nCould it be that the user provided the app credentials completely incorrectly, for an app that IS a store app?\nWait. The user showed the \"事件与回调\" console.\nWait... Could the plugin `openclaw-lark` be hitting `open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` and it's intercepting that? No.\nLet's check the Feishu configuration in `openclaw.json`.\nThe AppID is `cli_a95e7a8914ba5cc2`.\n\nWhat if the App ID the user has configured in `openclaw.json` (`cli_a95e7a8914ba5cc2`) does **NOT MATCH** the App they are currently looking at and editing in their browser?\nThis is a very common mistake! A user creates App A (\"My Bot\"), configures its AppID in OpenClaw, then goes to the Feishu developer console, creates App B (\"New Bot\"), edits the events, publishes it, but OpenClaw is still trying to connect using App A! App A was never published or is a Store App or has Webhook configured!\n\nLet's ask the user to double check:\nIs the AppID on the \"凭证与基础信息\" (Credentials & Basic Info) page of the app they *just published* exactly `cli_a95e7a8914ba5cc2`?\n\nI can ask the user nicely to verify this.\n\n`AppID`: `cli_a95e7a8914ba5cc2`\n\nAlso, wait... What if they created an app on LARKSUITE (overseas) and set the domain to `feishu` in the config? Or vice versa? `feishu` domain is `open.feishu.cn`. LARK is `open.larksuite.com`.\nThe user is in China based on timestamps (GMT+8) and uses Chinese. They are likely using Feishu.\n\nLet's check `open.feishu.cn` rules properly.\n\"receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app\"\nIs it possible the `openclaw-lark` plugin constructs the connection payload with a hardcoded AppID from somewhere else? No, `appId` comes from user config.\n\nLet's consider that the user DID publish. But the backend says \"No, you're not a self-built app or you're not configured\".\nWait. Look at the API being called: `https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping`\nWhy is it pinging `openclaw_bot`?\nIs `open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` an actual Feishu API?\nLet me curl it to see if it even exists on Feishu's servers, or if a typo in the plugin causes a bad request!\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7fe179a5e3a04778","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -I https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":1299,"output":733,"cacheRead":73041,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75073,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775565217536,"responseId":"chatcmpl-5264cc1d-fe86-424c-ba3e-2cf8de200e8a"}}
