{"type":"message","id":"ec86c0d0","parentId":"a832880c","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:34:01.310Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait, `openclaw_bot/ping` is a 404 on Feishu. Oh, wait... is the plugin configuring a webhook using some incorrect URL? No, wait wait wait. Could `bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` be an internal bot name that the plugin sets? No, the URL is `https://open.feishu.cn/...`. That's Feishu's domain.\n\nWait. A 400 Bad Request error. Not a 404. In the logs before, it was a 400! If I do a GET/HEAD (which `curl -I` does), it's a 404 probably because it's a POST endpoint and only exists dynamically? No, `open-apis` are standard. But I notice the exact error:\n`'receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in:\\n' + ...`\nThis looks like an OFFICIAL Feishu response from some other endpoint like `/open-apis/ws/v2/endpoints`, NOT from `/bot/v1/...ping`.\nLook closer at the log from earlier:\n```\n      url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n```\nWait! I've been seeing this in the `gateway.log` mixed with the Feishu error. Could they be from TWO completely different things? Like maybe `openclaw_bot` is something else, and the actual error `receive events or callbacks through...` is from the WS startup? Yes. `axios` prints its request objects when it crashes. Maybe there's a custom bot plugin making that `ping`? No... \nWait. Look at the ping body:\n`data: '{\"needBotInfo\":true}'`\nWait, does Feishu have an endpoint to ping a bot? No. But maybe OpenClaw's Lark plugin implements a custom ping? Let's check the code of the openclaw-lark plugin.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_53be9a14738697dd","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -R \"openclaw_bot/ping\" ~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":75992,"output":481,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite"