{"type":"message","id":"d0b12ea0","parentId":"814ece12","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:34:07.069Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aha! The plugin specifically tries to probe the bot identity via a hacky `bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` endpoint? Why would it do that?\nWait, if it does that, is that causing the error?\nNo, the plugin is just trying to get the bot's OpenID or something. But let's look at the actual error! The error is:\n`'receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in:\\n' + ...`\nWhere does THIS error come from?\nLet's search for this error in the Feishu documentation or in the plugin.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fa0267b570be53d9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -R \"receive events or callbacks through persistent connection\" ~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":3591,"output":178,"cacheRead":73042,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76811,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775565242676,"responseId":"chatcmpl-913a4db9-a62d-49c6-8091-ac4608dac193"}}
