{"type":"message","id":"b7c5be49","parentId":"294b679a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:34:20.267Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Oh my god!\n\"receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app\" is **NOT an error from the server**. It is a **hardcoded startup info banner printed by the official Lark SDK every single time it starts up** as a helpful reminder!!!\n\nSo the connection IS NOT being rejected with that message! That message is just a banner!\nThe real error is `Request failed with status code 400` inside the `axios` call to `/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` or somewhere else!\n\nLet's read the 400 error in the logs.\nThe 400 error was from `axios` trying to `POST https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping`.\nBut why does it try that, and why does it 400?\nAh! If the Feishu backend has no such endpoint, maybe it returned 404, but wait—I just curl'd it and it returned `404 Not Found`. So why `AxiosError: Request failed with status code 400` in the logs?\n\nActually, the error 400 could be from `/open-apis/ws/v2/endpoints`.\nIn the earlier log:\n```\n      method: 'post',\n      url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n      data: '{\"needBotInfo\":true}',\n```\nThis is explicitly 400.\nWait! Let me read `/Users/hh/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/src/core/lark-client.js`.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f8795f7d5149db15","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/hh/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/src/core/lark-client.js | grep -C 10 \"openclaw_bot/ping\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":4284,"output":438,"cacheRead":73029,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77751,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775565254159,"responseId":"chatcmpl-fefb6318-bc68-4566-a8bf-b470b97dc93b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"92fb773c","parentId":"b7c5be49","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:34:20.319Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f8795f7d5149db15","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"appId,\n                appSecret,\n                appType: Lark.AppType.SelfBuild,\n                domain: resolveBrand(this.account.brand),\n            });\n        }\n        return this._sdk;\n    }\n    // ---- Bot identity ----------------------------------------------------------\n    /**\n     * Probe bot identity via the `bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` API.\n     * Results are cached on the instance for subsequent access via\n     * `botOpenId` / `botName`.\n     */\n    async probe(opts) {\n        const maxAge = opts?.maxAgeMs ?? 0;\n        if (maxAge > 0 && this._lastProbeResult && Date.now() - this._lastProbeAt < maxAge) {\n            return this._lastProbeResult;\n        }\n        if (!this.account.appId || !this.account.appSecret) {\n            return { ok: false, error: 'missing credentials (appId, appSecret)' };\n        }\n        try {\n            const needBotInfo = opts?.needBotInfo ?? true;\n            const res = await this.sdk.request({\n                method: 'POST',\n                url: '/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n                data: { needBotInfo },\n            });\n            if (res.code !== 0) {\n                const result = {\n                    ok: false,\n                    appId: this.account.appId,\n                    error: `API error: ${res.msg || `code ${res.code}`}`,\n                };\n                this._lastProbeResult = result;\n                this._lastProbeAt = Date.now();"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14,"aggregated":"appId,\n                appSecret,\n                appType: Lark.AppType.SelfBuild,\n                domain: resolveBrand(this.account.brand),\n            });\n        }\n        return this._sdk;\n    }\n    // ---- Bot identity ----------------------------------------------------------\n    /**\n     * Probe bot identity via the `bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` API.\n     * Results are cached on the instance for subsequent access via\n     * `botOpenId` / `botName`.\n     */\n    async probe(opts) {\n        const maxAge = opts?.maxAgeMs ?? 0;\n        if (maxAge > 0 && this._lastProbeResult && Date.now() - this._lastProbeAt < maxAge) {\n            return this._lastProbeResult;\n        }\n        if (!this.account.appId || !this.account.appSecret) {\n            return { ok: false, error: 'missing credentials (appId, appSecret)' };\n        }\n        try {\n            const needBotInfo = opts?.needBotInfo ?? true;\n            const res = await this.sdk.request({\n                method: 'POST',\n                url: '/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n                data: { needBotInfo },\n            });\n            if (res.code !== 0) {\n                const result = {\n                    ok: false,\n                    appId: this.account.appId,\n                    error: `API error: ${res.msg || `code ${res.code}`}`,\n                };\n                this._lastProbeResult = result;\n                this._lastProbeAt = Date.now();","cwd":"/Users/hh/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775565260314}}
{"type":"message","id":"d10bf1f0","parentId":"92fb773c","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:34:28.164Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait! Is there an official API `/open-apis/bot/v1/info` and the openclaw_bot/ping is a typo?\nLet me check the official Feishu docs for bot info.\nThe bot info API is `GET /open-apis/bot/v3/info`.\nDid someone write `/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` for an openclaw plugin?\nWait, if it is a 404, axios might throw 400? No. Wait! If the tenant access token is invalid, the `request` function handles the Auth interceptor, and fetching the tenant access token from `/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal` might return 400 if the app Secret is WRONG or the app doesn't exist!!\n\nAh!!!! The `sdk.request` automatically fetches `tenant_access_token`. \nIf `tenant_access_token` fetching fails, the Feishu SDK might throw a 400 error!\nLet's trace `tenant_access_token`.\nLet's try to fetch `tenant_access_token` manually using curl to see what error Feishu returns for this AppID and Secret!\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a96e1fc1ced29357","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal \\\n-H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n-d '{\"app_id\":\"cli_a95e7a8914ba5cc2\", \"app_secret\":\"FnzZDL7YmMnFB2Pr1rXovcitjz6Cv13V\"}'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":1056,"output":381,"cacheRead":77085,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78522,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775565260320,"responseId":"chatcmpl-9f565cf5-5fd8-4203-8bb1-ca194a388399"}}
