{"type":"message","id":"0ab29c83","parentId":"356c26e8","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:34:50.123Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait, the SDK file might be `lib/services/ws/index.js`? Wait, I don't need to dig into the SDK internals for `endpoints`.\n\nLet's look at `gateway.log` again. The Axios error 400 is for:\n```\n      method: 'post',\n      url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping',\n```\nActually, wait, if I run `curl -X POST https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` I got `404 Not found`. But in Axios, if the backend returns `400 Bad Request` it means the endpoint *does* exist in some proxy but rejects the payload?\nWhy would OpenClaw plugin use `/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping`? Wait, maybe it's `openclaw_bot/ping` just to trigger a 404/400 specifically to test connectivity or get the Bot ID?\nActually, what if I send it with the token?\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_cae8d6f2048f7b96","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST -H \"Authorization: Bearer t-g10447kyBJLQXUUFGACXQQF2Q55T7YITDBFPDVJB\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"needBotInfo\":true}' https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":1838,"output":356,"cacheRead":77063,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79257,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775565284329,"responseId":"chatcmpl-0dcc9c89-993f-4842-9a3e-ec41bd4cc411"}}
