{"type":"message","id":"d7f46958","parentId":"1950cf93","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:35:23.366Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Okay. So the Feishu `400` error continues exactly as before for the WebSocket endpoint connection.\nWait!\nThe log shows:\n```\n2026-04-07T20:30:30.250+08:00 [error]: [ AxiosError: Request failed with status code 400 ... url: 'https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping' ]\n2026-04-07T20:30:30.252+08:00 [info]: [ 'event-dispatch is ready' ]\n2026-04-07T20:30:30.253+08:00 [info]: [ '[ws]', 'receive events or callbacks through persistent connection only available in self-build & Feishu app, Configured in:\\n' ... ]\n2026-04-07T20:30:30.769+08:00 [error]: [ '[ws]', 'Request failed with status code 400' ]\n2026-04-07T20:30:30.770+08:00 [error]: [ '[ws]', 'connect failed' ]\n```\nSo there are **TWO** 400 errors:\n1. The `openclaw_bot/ping` throws 400. This is probably just the `probe()` function in `openclaw-lark` trying to fail silently, but Axios throws and logs it loudly.\n2. The WebSocket connection *itself* throws 400:\n`[error]: [ '[ws]', 'Request failed with status code 400' ]`\n\nIf the WebSocket endpoint `/open-apis/ws/v2/endpoints` returns 400, it usually means:\n1. App is not published properly or has no events.\n2. The AppID belongs to a **Store App (商店应用)** instead of a **Self-built App (企业自建应用)**.\nWait! I told the user that 商店应用 can't use WebSocket. They didn't confirm they created a 企业自建应用.\nCould it be that they created a \"商店应用\" but the Feishu UI somehow presented them with the option to use Long Connection? Yes, that is totally possible. But Feishu's backend explicitly rejects it because Store Apps DO NOT support Long Connections!\nWait! Store App support for Long Connection was never released by Feishu.\nDid the user click **\"创建企业自建应用\"** (Create Custom App) or **\"创建商店应用\"** (Create Store App)?\nIf their URL in the browser is `https://open.feishu.cn/app/cli_...` it's hard to tell without knowing the app type.\n\nWait, another common reason: The Feishu developer console allows saving events, but if you do NOT add **any permissions** associated with those events, the event subscription is considered invalid!\nFor example: `im.message.receive_v1` (接收消息) requires the permission: **\"获取单聊、群组消息\"** (Get private and group messages) AND **\"获取与发送单聊、群组消息\"** (Read and Send messages).\nIF the user added the event but DID NOT go to the \"权限管理\" (Permissions and Scopes) tab to request these permissions, the Feishu backend might consider the App's configuration broken or invalid, and return 400.\n\nWait, another possibility. The user showed a screenshot of \"事件与回调\" page.\nIs there any other problem?\nMaybe the IP address issue? WebSocket connections don't require IP whitelists.\nWhat about `Encrypt Key` (消息加密密钥)? In the \"事件与回调\" page, there is an Encrypt Key setting. If the user typed an Encrypt Key but didn't put it in `openclaw.json`, then Feishu WebSocket connection will actually fail? No, Feishu SDK would handle it or receive encrypted payloads.\n\nLet's look at what the user wrote:\n`[Tue 2026-04-07 20:33 GMT+8] 已发布，已上线，你看下日志` (Published, online, look at logs).\nAnd my logs STILL show `Request failed with status code 400`.\n\nIs there a chance that `appSecret` is just incorrect?\nWait! In the previous turn I curl'd `tenant_access_token` with the provided `appSecret` and it **SUCCEEDED** (`code: 0`). So the `appId` and `appSecret` are 100% correct.\n\nThen I curl'd `https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping` with the exact token and it **SUCCEEDED** returning `pingBotInfo`.\nWhy did it succeed in curl but throw 400 in OpenClaw logs???\nLet's check the curl response again.\nWait!\n```\ncurl -s -X POST -H \"Authorization: Bearer t-g10447kyBJLQXUUFGACXQQF2Q55T7YITDBFPDVJB\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"needBotInfo\":true}' https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping\n{\"code\":0,\"msg\":\"\",\"data\":{\"pingBotInfo\":{\"botID\":\"ou_760c4bed06025043478956c9ac7e01e4\",\"botName\":\"openclaw\"}}}\n```\nThis was a successful curl request.\nBut in the OpenClaw Axios logs:\n`{\"code\":\"ERR_BAD_REQUEST\",\"status\":400}`\nWhy did Axios get 400?\n\nLet's look at the OpenClaw Axios request headers:\n```\n      _header: 'POST /open-apis/bot/v1/openclaw_bot/ping HTTP/1.1\\r\\n' +\n        'Accept: application/json, text/plain, */*\\r\\n' +\n        'Content-Type: application/json\\r\\n' +\n        'User-Agent: openclaw-lark/2026.4.1/mac\\r\\n' +\n        'Content-Length: 20\\r\\n' +\n        'Accept-Encoding: gzip, compress, deflate, br\\r\\n' +\n        'Host: open.feishu.cn\\r\\n' +\n        'Connection: keep-alive\\r\\n' +\n        '\\r\\n',\n```\nNotice anything missing?\n**THERE IS NO AUTHORIZATION HEADER!!!**\n`Axios` sent the request WITHOUT `Authorization: Bearer ...`!\nIf the `Authorization` header is missing, Feishu will obviously throw a `400 Bad Request` or `401 Unauthorized` (Feishu sometimes returns 400 for missing auth).\n\nBut wait, why is the WebSocket `connect` ALSO throwing 400?\n```\n2026-04-07T20:30:30.769+08:00 [error]: [ '[ws]', 'Request failed with status code 400' ]\n2026-04-07T20:30:30.770+08:00 [error]: [ '[ws]', 'connect failed' ]\n```\nIs the WebSocket SDK ALSO failing to send the Authorization header?\nWhy would the SDK fail to get a token?\nBecause to get a token, the SDK makes a request to `/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal`.\nIF that request fails, the SDK will proceed without a token, and the API requests will return 400!\n\nWait, why would the SDK fail to get a token?\nAh! Let's check `lark.secrets.json` AGAIN.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6c362784f276db0d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/credentials/lark.secrets.json"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":7228,"output":1845,"cacheRead":77075,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86148,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775565305900,"responseId":"chatcmpl-15434532-908c-4be6-999f-35dc6ff5ebf4"}}
