{"type":"message","id":"bcbe70b2","parentId":"806dab19","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:35:27.703Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Okay, so `lark.secrets.json` looks good. \nLet's check `openclaw.json` again.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_385b3155fc795ac7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | grep -i \"lark-secrets\" -C 5"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":5063,"output":65,"cacheRead":81139,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86267,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775565323421,"responseId":"chatcmpl-047faf00-3b98-4d53-a15f-9bbc0505f0d3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a501b795","parentId":"bcbe70b2","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:35:27.755Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_385b3155fc795ac7","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"feishu\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"appId\": \"cli_a95e7a8914ba5cc2\",\n      \"appSecret\": {\n        \"source\": \"file\",\n        \"provider\": \"lark-secrets\",\n        \"id\": \"lark.appSecret\"\n      },\n      \"domain\": \"feishu\",\n      \"connectionMode\": \"websocket\",\n      \"requireMention\": true,\n--\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"secrets\": {\n    \"providers\": {\n      \"lark-secrets\": {\n        \"source\": \"file\",\n        \"path\": \"~/.openclaw/credentials/lark.secrets.json\"\n      }\n    }\n  }"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":14,"aggregated":"\"feishu\": {\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"appId\": \"cli_a95e7a8914ba5cc2\",\n      \"appSecret\": {\n        \"source\": \"file\",\n        \"provider\": \"lark-secrets\",\n        \"id\": \"lark.appSecret\"\n      },\n      \"domain\": \"feishu\",\n      \"connectionMode\": \"websocket\",\n      \"requireMention\": true,\n--\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"secrets\": {\n    \"providers\": {\n      \"lark-secrets\": {\n        \"source\": \"file\",\n        \"path\": \"~/.openclaw/credentials/lark.secrets.json\"\n      }\n    }\n  }","cwd":"/Users/hh/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775565327750}}
{"type":"message","id":"26051d20","parentId":"a501b795","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:35:33.976Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait, is `openclaw-lark` expecting `lark.appSecret` or something else?\nThe reference `{\"source\":\"file\", \"provider\":\"lark-secrets\", \"id\":\"lark.appSecret\"}` uses the JSONPath `lark.appSecret` inside the secrets file.\nIf the secrets file is:\n```json\n{\n  \"lark\": {\n    \"appSecret\": \"FnzZDL7YmMnFB2Pr1rXovcitjz6Cv13V\"\n  }\n}\n```\nDoes OpenClaw correctly extract the secret?\nWait! IN openclaw 2026.4.x, does `id: lark.appSecret` mean it looks for `{\"lark.appSecret\": \"...\"}` or does it resolve dot-notation `{\"lark\": {\"appSecret\": \"...\"}}`?\nAh!!! OpenClaw's secret provider might NOT resolve dot-notation for `id`! It might literally look for the string key `\"lark.appSecret\"` at the top level of the JSON file!\nLet me check this by providing the secret flatly.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a0fc2073db2eafc2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/credentials/lark.secrets.json"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":1260,"output":276,"cacheRead":85189,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86725,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775565327756,"responseId":"chatcmpl-152eddb8-7d6f-40a0-b0b3-fc1a3a57402b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e8e3a30","parentId":"26051d20","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:35:34.028Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a0fc2073db2eafc2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"lark\": {\n    \"appSecret\": \"FnzZDL7YmMnFB2Pr1rXovcitjz6Cv13V\"\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":11,"aggregated":"{\n  \"lark\": {\n    \"appSecret\": \"FnzZDL7YmMnFB2Pr1rXovcitjz6Cv13V\"\n  }\n}","cwd":"/Users/hh/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775565334022}}
{"type":"message","id":"2f0a94d2","parentId":"8e8e3a30","timestamp":"2026-04-07T12:35:39.246Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let's modify `lark.secrets.json` to have `\"lark.appSecret\": \"...\"` at the top level just in case, or change `openclaw.json` to use `\"id\": \"appSecret\"` and the file to `{\"appSecret\": \"...\"}`.\nIf OpenClaw wasn't getting the secret, the `appSecret` given to the SDK would be `undefined`.\nIf `appSecret` is `undefined`, the Feishu SDK will try to fetch the token with `app_secret: undefined`, which Feishu rejects with a HTTP 400 Bad Request (\"app_secret missing or invalid\")!!!\nThen the SDK fails to get the token, and the subsequent API calls (like `openclaw_bot/ping` and WebSocket connect) all get 400!\n\nLet me prove this!\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4d31a9d34ee7f4d0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal \\\n-H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n-d '{\"app_id\":\"cli_a95e7a8914ba5cc2\"}'"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-high","usage":{"input":1597,"output":266,"cacheRead":85182,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87045,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775565334029,"responseId":"chatcmpl-93686b58-9d13-46ba-b8c4-0a444dd792a1"}}
